			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Saw this over at the Beastlord boards. I liked it, so I'm bringing it here.
<br />

<br />
What are the top things you see 'broken' or not functioning correctly for Magicians?
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">This is NOT a Class Balance thread.</span></span>
<br />
This thread should deal directly with skills, spells and or abilities Magicians currently have that do not function correctly in some manner. Posts not relating to magician-specific skills, spells, or abilities will be deleted. Posts asking to rebalance the class (such as making nukes more powerful) or asking for quest alterations (like making Quillmane's cloak droppable) will be deleted.
<br />

<br />
Bugs that are quoted above will have their post deleted, keeping the "clutter" of this thread down (simple is better).
<br />

<br />
An example:
<br />

<br />
Focused Monster Summoning IV regen isn't in-line with other focused pets.
<br />

<br />
Do you know of an AA, Spell or Ability not working right?
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Please remember to /bug any bugs you discover!</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Fixed Bugs</span>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>xalmat wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Transon's Phantasmal Protection and Xegony's Phantasmal Guard are overwritten by Phantom Armor and Phantasmal Armor.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Fixed on the March 23, 2004 patch. Transon's and Xegony's are altered to have more HP regen than Phantom and Phantasmal Armor. This prevents Transon's and Xegony's from being overwritten by the rest of the Phantom Armor series.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Anduran the Artisan wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Elemental Siphon Critting and doing double damage to pet.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Fixed with the March 23, 2004 patch. Elemental Draw won't crit either.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Xalmat wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Focused Monster Summoning IV regen isn't in-line with other focused pets.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
"Fixed" with the March 25, 2004 patch.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>xalmat wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Minion of Darkness (Gloves of Dark Summoning) doesn't grant the HP regen that Summoner's Boon (Diamond Prism of Companionship) does.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
"Fixed" with the March 25, 2004 patch.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Guest on Sun Mar 28, 2004 9:42 pm; edited 15 times in total</span></td>
