<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Izudin wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Elemental Durability "seems" to just add a hp buffer to the newly summoned pet instead of giving the pet the hp directly. This means that a pet wont have the full hp when summoned (or rather the original hp).
<br />

<br />
For example, I have ED1 which gives 2% more hp to the pet, and all pets I summon appear with 98% health when summoned.
<br />

<br />
The pet then regenerates to full, but this means that ED is quite useless for chaining pets (since you generally wont have time to let the new pet regen up to full before sending it into the fight).</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Seems to be a bug related to the way Natural Durability (in all forms) is handled. You experience a similar problem when you equip an item with a lot of HP (with ND3, a 100 HP item gives 110, but when equipped your current HP only goes up 100 while your max goes up 110).
