Working as intended Enomdar. Focused air hits 85, unfocused hits 83.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Wanderkind wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Bolt of flame often tells me it's doing damage, takes my mana, but has no spell effect  and mob takes no actual damage.  Only seems to work when I am extremely close to mob and it is on same height level as myself</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
This has to do with the nature of bolts. Since bolt graphics are broken, you can't "see" the bolt fly towards your target and hit any obstacles. Despite this however, bolts behave just like arrows, and are subject to running into objects, players, zone geometry, or even other monsters than its intended target. Working as intended.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Traigos-MM wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">3) Some pet spells require the pet to be targeted whereas others do not.  For example, frenzied burnout does not require your pet to be targeted wheras burnout does.  In general it would be better if pet spells could take affect on the pet without requiring the mage to retarget.
<br />

<br />
5) The damage from elemental siphon appears as nuke damage in a log.  This makes it difficult to parse damage.  It would be better if no damage were listed at all.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I'm dubious to call either of these bugs, but rather feature requests. Kind of agree on the Siphon bit though.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>itchyban wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Epic not focused by SoAS (if so intended)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
