			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is something I noticed last night in Plane of Earth.  We were attempting one of the ring events, and it was bugged up.  Some of the mobs ended up being in other areas of the zone.  I casted Suspend Minion 2 and put my pet in my pocket and loaded up Eye of Tallon.  After about 2-3 casts, I still hadn't found any of the mobs yet.  On the last eye cast, I noticed one of my buffs was dropping, no big deal really.  The buff drops, and I continue to look around.  The buff icon for Eye starts to flash and it goes out.  But my sight didn't return to my character.  I casted another Eye, and an eye spawned in that spot, which quickly dropped beneath the world.  After about 2 minutes of waiting, I was just about to log off and back in, when my sight returned to my character.
<br />

<br />
After noticing this, I did some testing.  I found that if a buff drops off from you naturally, your sight binds wherever Eye of Tallon stops at when it's timer runs out.  I tried clicking off a buff with an eye summoned, and my sight returns just fine.  It seems to only be when another buff's timer runs out.  My sight returned every time after 2 minutes.
<br />

<br />
After I noticed this bug, I did a bug report in game stating what I just typed here.  Might as well get this a little more exposure here.  8)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=221279" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jimbop</a>
<br />
70 Arch Mage
<br />
<a href="http://www.eotdraiders.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eye of the Deceiver</a>
<br />
Vazaelle Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
