				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The range bugs I mentioned are not an issue with vector distance, as asserted above. 
<br />

<br />
The issues are most notable when close to the projection point of the mob unto the plane of the mage, but a moderate positive or negative height differential exists. Simply "circling around" the mob to an elevation similar to the mob confirms this and can be easily demonstrated "on the wall" of a zone such as PoV or The Grey.
<br />

<br />
In all cases, the vector distance is within range and other spells with the same or lesser ranges hit just fine.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Elementalist Itchyban of Veeshan</a>
