			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">a) Mage pets have a huge melee box, this nearly always prevents them from attacking in close. Proximity afects aggro, ergo mage pets almost never draw aggro off other pets...which is bad when you want the mage pet to be the tank in a pet group.
<br />

<br />
b) luclin graphics for elementals prevent use of a horse (game balance), but the air, fire and water models have bad geometry in that they equip weapons in their *wrists*. Ergo thos e models should be redone, ala the luclin earth pet, which is humanoid, wields weapons correctly (or seems so) has legs and looks good.
<br />

<br />
c) Mage summoned staffs are *still* 2hb when they were supposed to have been made 1hb ages ago...2hb= ultra useless.
<br />

<br />
d) when giving pets weapons, you can't be sure what hand the item is in because they seem to switch them. For example say you give a pet a gnoll lariat, then later give it a summoned sword, it may end up switching the whip to its off hand...but you can't be sure if that's real or merely a graphic glitch. This is an issue incase you want to keep a special prc weapon in the main hand, where it will proc more often.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304331" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: red">REDORIOUS.....ARCHMAGE.....KARANA</span></span></a>
